caption: So elegant and classy. Service was great and the food even better. I enjoyed the crawfish pie.
Best food I've had in NOLA. I had the Buffalo frog legs (which were falling off the bone), shrimp & grits, and Ultimate Bloody Mary. Amazing!

Great bunch menu. The raw oysters and oysters Rockefeller were amazing. The shrimp and grits got high praise from others at the table. The blue crab omelette was delicious too. They also have $12 bottomless mimosas and Bloody Marys. Highly recommend.
Ask for my buddy Joesph! He’s my favorite vegetarian 😉! So nice and welcoming
Good place, we especially liked the variety of chargrilled oysters here - very delicious!
Food ok. Very covid safe

OMG Trenasse....Trenasse OMG! Listen. I'm from MD....so of course I had to get gumbo! The GUMBO is better than any thing up north...(not saying a lot) but better than a very popular place here in NO (neyo's). Char-grilled chicken, sausage and maybe even the vegetables! It was Bourbon Street in me mouth!

I came here just craving a burger. My wife had the taco Tuesday special. These appear to be simple dishes a mortal human would enjoy at any restaurant. But this would be your first mistake. I have never in my life, experienced a burger like this. If you are in New Orleans and staying or visiting anywhere near the French Quarter, it is a must, to eat here. Simple words cannot describe how delicious the food is and I am quite aware I am speaking in hyperbole.
Food was decent. Staff was good, and the apps were mediocre. Out of all the amazing food I've had in NOLA this wouldn't be at the top of my list to revisit.
Amazing atmosphere and food. Very professional staff.
The most delicious gumbo and bbq shrimp!! Highly enjoyed our meal here. We sat outside on a chilly night but there were outdoor heaters so we were still cozy.
Great service
If you order the grits, make sure you bring salt. Oysters were great but had some shells.

Very surprised about how great this was. I was, for some reason, expecting mediocre food and service but it was exceptional.  The prices are very reasonable for what you get. Love the fowl gumbo, house salad,  boudin hash, bloody mary, and the grits and grillades. Good covid protocols in place.

Amazing food and even better service! Our server made sure to ask if we were on a tight schedule and was very attentive.They don't joke around with their bottomless mimosas--we never had empty glasses. Highly recommend stopping in for brunch and getting the ham & cheese omelette or the 3-spread of bennys.
Fantastic service and food!! We had the Mardi Gras menu and added a few extra items and it was a perfect meal for us. We felt safe as all the staff were following the protocols plus some!

Was greeted with a friendly staff. I came in knowing what I wanted to order. I saw the fried Brie burger on the menu and had no choice but to order such an amazing dish. Beautiful presentation that makes it hard to think about anything but the burger before you. Would highly recommend if you want to feel like remy from the hit movie ratatouille when he tries a strawberry. Flavors will be floating in front of you because of how apparent they are in the dish. Not a drug but close enough. If you do not want to feel like this don’t come here and definitely don’t order this burger. You don’t deserve it.

Greeted with a friendly and classy staff. Make a reservation! Great selection of wine. I recommend the bubbly to pair well with raw oysters. I had the redfish. She had the Stinky Stew. Both dishes were absolutely incredible, but she made the better of the two choices. Highly recommend!
I ordered the pan seared red fish and it was very good. This restaurant has a great vibe.
Really tasty, clean food, amazing oysters.  Warm, friendly, anticipatory service.  Clearly well-managed.  Looking forward to a repeat visit!
Been eating here for years, the quality and service has always been excellent
The food and service were both great! My spouse and I loved all the food and the drinks were amazing as well.
Just fantastic!  We were looking for tasty New Orleans fare, and this place got it done.  Quality ingredients, amazing taste and kind service.  Loved my meal!  Would definitely return!

Paul, you are an all star!!! Thank you so much for such a great experience. The food here is wonderful! You don’t want to miss this experience if you are here visiting. We were making a choice between here and another place. We don’t feel we missed anything from visiting here! They covered it all! Thank you so much!
Nice little restaurant. They do a good job.
Rude service. My crackers were thrown on the table while others’ were served with a plate. If I didn’t look into waiter’s eye, he totally forgot me like I won’t spend a penny here.
Always amazing happy hour!
Food is great here. Some of the best oysters I've had, ever. The food server, which I may add looked just like Sal from Impractical Jokers lol, was very nice!

First level of the Intercontinental hotel. Great food, honestly. Started with their fried Brie burger—juicy and flavorful—and tastier when the Brie is drizzled on the burger. Moved to the green goddess wedge—a fun history to research. Eagerly awaited the crawfish etouffee which was so delicious alongside the cheesy grits. Sweetened the meal with their lemon crack cake, and washed the dinner down with a stiff sazerac. Always a treat to find such a restaurant when visiting New Orleans.

Went to Trenasse for Sunday brunch and it was absolutely amazing. I got the shrimp and grits and bottomless mimosas and the entree was the best shrimp and grits I’ve ever eaten. The mimosas were constantly being refilled by our amazing server. Derek was our server and he was absolutely great. Will definitely be back in the future.
Great food. Love their Martinis. You should  try baked oysters.  Thank you for service
Amazing food and service!

FOOD WAS AMAZING! We were sitting outside and there was a large party. We could tell the waitress was new but Paul May, the GM, went above and beyond to make our dining experience a memorable one. Highly recommend and will most definitely be returning ! Thanks Paul and thanks trenasse!

What an excellent find! The restaurant is in the Intercontinental Hotel and has amazing happy hour menu + super yummy food with good selection on their regular Keanu. We had fresh oversees (great) and a lot of charred oysters (pretty good but were missing wood charr taste). We also got very yummy shrimp from their happy hour menu. The seafood soup looked amazing as well but we were too full to get. It’s very well priced for the amount of seafood you get. Overall, I highly recommend Trenasse for happy hour or dinner.
Excellent Top Notch Service
Cozy but the hostesses attire needs to be upgraded immediately
Great service here and great oyster! Their happy hour has very fresh oyster, it is only $9 and amazing martini! Recommend this place

We were recommended to this restaurant by the hotel we are staying at. We enjoyed the food so much and highly recommend this restaurant. The International Oysters are fantastic if you like char-grilled Oysters. The Crawfish Pot Pie is spectacular and so is the Chocolate Sea Salt Tort.  We like to try different restaurants each night and went to Luke's Oyster Bar and Grill across the street and was completely disappointed in their menu that we left and came back to Trenasse for a 2nd night. Had the Stinky Stew and it was awesome.  Totally recommend this restaurant. Five stars 🌟

This is an amazing restaurant, tipical New Orleans food, with excellent taste and gourmet presentation. The attention is super fast and professional. Enjoy the happy hour offers!!! Highly recommended!!! They reopen on Nov 24, 2020 after been clsed due to Covid 19.

This was the tastiest meal of our three-day trip to New Orleans. My number one was the broiled oysters.  Unfortunately my wife had a little intestinal distress after this meal, possibly due to seafood étouffé (filling reheated?) or the oysters (msg?). I think she would still return, just be sure to order a little more carefully, the flavors were so good.
Great bar service, and the Sauteed Escargot appetizer was excellent!  Butter, garlic, mushrooms, and red wine sauce.....YUM!
Amazing food!!! And great drinks

Great food! The happy hour plates are unbelievable and you can make an outstanding meal out of them!

Bottomless mimosas are a must for brunch. I enjoyed the Jimmy poboy while my date enjoyed the Benedict trio. Both dishes were fantastic. Young crowd for brunch with excellent service. Would definitely recommend for out of towners.
Great food and service!!!

The food was excellent.  We tried the oyster sampler and three of the main entrees.  Everything was very flavorful.  We averaged about $40 per plate, but it was very good.  The presentation on the whole fish was incredible and it was cooked perfectly.  I would definitely eat here again.

The fried oyster salad was great! I only wish they could cut the lettuce into smaller pieces. The service was okay. Food prep took a while even though the restaurant was not busy at the time. The price is relatively expensive but acceptable.
Good food great location

Their crawfish pie did not disappoint! All 4 of us ordered them and we were all glad we did. The side salads and soups were also great. I definitely recommend going here even if you aren't a guest at the hotel.

Awful waiter. I ordered a steak medium and the steak was near blue. The poboy was bad. The bouidin balls tasted off. The crawfish pie had grits on it even though it was not listed. The bbq shrimp were overcooked. The side of fries were burnt.  Never going back

Went with 12 people for a birthday brunch- made reservations well in advance and they had a separate room for us, it worked out perfectly! It was absolutely the most amazing brunch the entire group has had, the Benny, Benny, Benny was outstanding, and the bottomless mimosas were excellent as well! Our group also raved about the fowl gumbo!

Nice bar, felt like the locals were coming in and relaxing and having a drink. Happy hour was good value for money and only a short walk to the main streets where you'd find bars and other restaurants.

Wow. I had been across the street to see if we could walk in to a seafood restaurant I knew. A 45 minute wait, and I looked across the street. Thank goodness! A quieter, friendly environment with an intriguing and innovative menu, good wine list, great service; and I am a new big fan of Trenasse!

Fantastic brunch and happy hour deals in a very nice setting with outstanding service. Highly recommended for the bottomless mimosas and brunch items--the duck confit salad, crab bisque, and shrimp and grits were all excellent. We happened to be late enough at brunch to get happy hour oysters at the end of the meal, which were a great deal, although we prefer smaller oysters in general. Overall a wonderful experience, brightened by our awesome server Chad, that I would recommend to anyone.
Food tastes good with excellent service.

Highly recommend this restaurant! My husband and I made a reservation for a late brunch and we were seated right away. Our waiter (Alfred J, per our receipt) was fantastic. We ordered the bottomless mimosas and our glasses never got below half full. Can't beat that for $10! The food was great.

The food was pretty fresh and strong at Trenasse as well as the tasty margaritas we had. We went for their Taco Tuesday special and enjoyed how fresh the beef taquitos were with real slabs of beef rather than just using a ground varietal.  The rest of the food we had was pretty tasty as well. The kitchen did send out our taco salad missing a few items than what they had listed in the menu but they quickly rectified that by bringing those items out.  I removed a star here for two reasons, the first is the ambiance and atmosphere which is nothing special, probably the only notable and likable thing about their atmosphere were the tables, they were neat cuts of wood with a smooth glazed top. The other reason for removing a star was an inconsistency in service. We went during shift change, so having two servers and being passed off wasn’t really an issue, our first server Ayana was stellar and really great, our second server Eric was good at his job yet definitely had trouble knowing when to hold them and when to fold them.  Eric liked to quite often linger but not have anything interesting to say, he would just linger and kind of be seeking us to engage, but without anything interesting to rebound off of it just wasn’t working out.

I would have liked to rate Trenasse 3.5 stars, but because of the service and atmosphere, I think this place is better than 3 stars. I visited Trenasse for a group brunch on a Saturday afternoon. Our server was excellent! I ordered the Boudin Hash and Eggs. When it arrived, it was visually appealing. The hash had good flavor, but they were super stingy with the potatoes. It was also just barely warm. My syrup was the hottest thing on my plate. The eggs were bland even with the cheese added. The bacon was delicious. The menu said it was sweet bacon, but it tasted more like a peppery bacon. Either way, I loved it! The biscuit was weird. It had the potential to be good, but was a bit too salty and the bottom half was dry. Overall, it was a decent breakfast and I would probably get it again.

Exceptional. 6 stars. Prices were reasonable for the standard here, food was fresh and unique, artfully crafted and presented. I had the oyster salad with vinaigrette dressing with smokey sauce and crispy oysters with crispy green beans and sweet potato flakes and sweet corn. Ribe eye and filet also enjoyed at the table.

This review is hard for me to write. Not because it was bad but I just don't want to write out all the things I was impressed with.  So, here's what I will say. We had a party of 7 for a family gathering. Our server was top notch, checking in with us periodically, staying on top of our drinks, delivering food quickly. We ate pretty much one of everything on the menu between all of us and I couldn't be more impressed with the quality of the food. This is by far and away worth it and not at all what I was expecting out of a hotel restaurant. This place easily deserves a spot in my top 10 all time dining experiences.  Special highlights: 1) Stinky's Stew is stinky only in name. So much delicious food in a bowl. 2) Taste of Trenasse was on point. Everyone who got it, 4 people, were in love with it. Some of us just decided to roll with the food that was delivered, even though it wasn't what was ordered. Boudin balls were really good. BBQ shrimp just ok. The crispy shrimp was better. Taste of trenass let's you try three dishes: lamb, crawfish pie and redfish - all three were delicious! On the dessert side got to try most of the desserts and the creme brulee and the pie topped with strawberries were the standouts.

I was looking for a restaurant that was open on a Monday evening and had certain foods. This one fit the bill. I was surprised that it was in the Intercontinental Hotel and was ready to be very disappointed. Sometimes hotel restaurants are not the best. However this restaurant had good food and a lively ambiance. The service was at times a bit slow. Perhaps that was because so many other places are closed on Monday evenings. The food was good. They served pork crackins. I had raw oysters on the half shell and a filet mignon. The prices reflected the quality. This was not an outstanding restaurant, but it served my needs that Monday evening and the food was good.

On the evening of the P!NK concert, I wasn't having luck being able to secure any dinner reservations (understandably) in the vicinity of the MBSD before 9pm until I was lucky enough to stumble across Trenasse via Googe search results. Via Google's own reservation platform I was able to secure a table for 4 at 5:30pm (precisely the time slot I was looking for). Triumphant, I arranged to have family driving in from out of town to attend the concert as well to meet us at Trenasse for dinner.  That feeling of triumph at having found a table paled in comparison to the absolute delight our meal, along with our service at the table, turned out to be. Being a relative local to the area, I am surprised I haven't heard of this place before! Amongst our group, we enjoyed the crispy boudin balls, the debris fries and catfish nuggets as appetizers and for the entrees we dined on the steak, the rabbit fricassee, and the lamb chops.  Every single dish was to die for! I cannot wait to go back and try more of the incredible menu Trenasse has to offer. As a side-note: the pleasure our server seemed to get out of telling us the backstory on the "Stinky" moniker, when asked, was worth the trip alone 😂. Just do yourself a favor and pay Trenasse a visit; I guarantee your tastebuds will thank you.

The mains and dessert were partially served and one or two people always waited an additional 10-12 minutes until their food arrived so the rest of us were polite and allowed our meals to get cold while we waited.
